caption:
Leave a legacy, not a trace ⛰️

We all have a role to play to treat the great outdoors with respect, so we can return to the same beautiful spot again. When we are not mindful of our impact, the places we love can be significantly damaged for ourselves and future generations.

Here’s how to safeguard our beautiful lands, from the @nationalparkservice on its 7 Leave No Trace Principles:
- Plan ahead and prepare
- Travel and camp on durable surfaces
- Dispose of waste properly
- Leave what you find
- Minimize campfire impacts
- Respect wildlife
- Be considerate of other visitors
There is a beautiful world to explore - let’s do it with the respect nature deserves!
#leavenotrace

caption:
Change the way you travel ✈️
Here are 3 ways to travel more intentionally this Summer.

1. Take your time
Just because you’ve been there once, doesn’t mean you’ve seen it all before. Return to the places and people you love this Summer with an open mind and a fresh perspective.

2. Know your impact
Be mindful of how tourism is impacting your destination. Make good choices that support the local economy and environment.

3. Offset your trip
We’ve teamed up with Cool Effect to help you offset your travels. 100% of each offset goes towards planting trees and protecting forests to assist in carbon capture

caption:
Today we took the day off. To spend time outside, with family, friends or just ourselves. To breathe the fresh air we are privileged to breathe and to appreciate the beauty of our planet.

At ADAY, #earthday is everyday. We believe in the power of every choice we make, 365 days of the year. So that we can continue to create the future we want and raise the standard for clothing and our industry. There is so much work to be done, and we are ready for it. But today, we celebrate 🌎💚

If you need a reminder to get out and do the same, this is it.

Happy Earth Day. 

Love, Team Aday

caption:
Outfit repeating is good for the planet + your wallet 🙌 learn more👇

Wearing your clothes 50x instead of 5 reduces carbon emissions by 400% per item, per year 🌎

caption:
Imagine men trying to tell women what they can and cannot do with their bodies, oh wait 🙄 it is actually happening...
.
.
.
𝐄𝐚𝐫𝐥𝐢𝐞𝐫 𝐭𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐲𝐞𝐚𝐫: The newly instated Texas Heartbeat Act prohibits abortion from as early as 6 weeks into a woman's pregnancy. Before this, elective abortions were allowed up to 20 weeks post-fertilization giving women much more time to make the decision that was right for them.

𝐉𝐮𝐬𝐭 𝐥𝐚𝐬𝐭 𝐰𝐞𝐞𝐤: The Supreme Court met to discuss if the state of Mississippi could ban abortions at 15 weeks gestation. This case is deemed one of the most important abortion rights cases since Roe v Wade and is set for June 2022. We will be tuning in.

𝐎𝐮𝐫 𝐯𝐢𝐞𝐰: Her body. Her choice. The end.

✨Check out our stories today to see how you can help make a change

caption:
We’re so happy to see the world opening back up again, but we can’t celebrate the joy of travel without bringing awareness to the complexities our queer community faces when traveling. 

We love to travel because it gives us the chance to experience different cultures, people, perspectives + places. However, for queer travelers, safety is a big concern. In 70+ countries homosexuality is still criminalized and even punishable by death in parts of the world (USA today). A recent survey commissioned by Orbitz, found that more than a quarter of 2,000 queer Americans polled said they feel the need to downplay their identity while traveling. 

Head over to our stories for resources to learn more about queer travel + ways to support. And thank you @thenomadicmars for sharing your story with us. 🏳️‍🌈
